NAME

  ltod - translates Linux formatted text files into DOS formatted text files

SYNOPSIS

  ltod (flags)

DESCRIPTION

  ltod is designed to translate a Linux formatted text file into a DOS formatted
  text file. ltod will translate each line feed end of line character sequence
  to a carriage return + line feed end of line character sequence.

FLAGS

  -h  display the flags that can be interpreted by ltod
  -i  input file
  -o  output file
  -v  display version
  -s  report statistics
  -w  write over mode (input file will be overwritten as output)

  Standard input and output are assumed if no file names were specified.

